Diagnosis.
Anterolateral margin of pronotum yellow without solid black stripe. Cicatrices with dark brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
Fig. 18I
). Anterolateral margin with some brown punctures. Male (
Fig. 5
A–C). Pygophore with dorsal rim widely excavated (
Fig. 5A
). Superior process of genital cup short, half-moon shaped; next to dorsal rim (
Fig. 5B
). Paramere with a single lobe curved anteriorly, tapering and elongated, margin rounded; stalk cylindrical with a small carina on inner side continuing along anterior lobe (
Fig. 5B
). Proctiger with laterodorsal tufts of setae separated by wide ridge; posterior face ogival (
Fig. 5B,C
). Ventral rim with expansions rounded, slightly tumid, short, almost level with posterolateral angles in ventral view (
Fig. 5C
); base of each expansion with a conspicuous transverse carina (
Fig. 5A,B
). Female (
Fig. 5D
). Gonocoxites 8 posterior margin sinuous, slanting, inner angle rounded; sutural border divergent from basal third, gonapophyses 8 slightly exposed.
